                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">Policeman</hi> 349 <hi rend="italic">M</hi>). I took the prisoner into custody on 15th July at Mr. Carter's shop, where he was detained for uttering another</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="187808060065"></xptr>
               <p>forged order—he said at first that his brother gave it him, and afterwards that it was given him by a man named Cole living in Mile End Road—at the station, in the cell where he was, I found this other order, dated 17th July—the prisoner was wearing a pair of boots which he got as part of the last goods he obtained.</p>
               <p>C. T. <hi rend="largeCaps">SMITH</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Re-examined</hi>). This order appears to be in a similar writing to the others.</p>
